8:
You're all bruised up... Wait here for
a second—
10:
...It... It's all my fault. I'm a bad son.
My d-dad didn't do anything!
12:
But you're hurt, aren't you?
I don't want you to feel like you're
alone.
14:
Hey, let's go play! I'm Mary. What's
your name?
27: Whoa, WHAT?! I'm gonna be late!
33:
I'm sorry, Mary! Did I keep you
waiting long?
36: N-no, not at all! You're early, actually!
43: Wh-why did you call this... a date?
47:
I messed up back on the beach the
other day...
51:
But this time... I made up my mind.
I'm not going to run away...
54:
A-anyway, should we go for a little
walk? We haven't been out together
in a while!
57:
Uh, um... Y-yeah, sure... L-let's do
that!
70:
So you're saying that those sheep
react to people's emotions and act
on their own?
73:
Yeah. The Guild was curious about
the sheep, so they tasked me with
researching them.
75:
Who knows why they're equipped
with such a function in the first
place. I wonder which specific
emotions they've been taking in—
79:
S-s-sorry, Mary! I don't know when
to stop talking...
83:
It's okay, Will. I like hearing you talk
about things! I could listen to you all
day, even...
86:
...Hey, do you remember that time
we talked on this bridge when we
were little?
90:
...I just wanted to see you smile. I felt
bad that I could only make you that
stupid doll, though...
94:
It wasn't stupid. It made me happy,
Will! So happy I almost cried...
96:
I hid from everyone how lonely I was
back then... But you saw right
through me.
99: You've been there for me all along.
107:
Will, even if this isn't what you want...
Even if you're happy with the way
things have been until now! I, I...
114:
...You've been there for me all along,
too. That's why...
116:
Oh, let me get to the point... M-Mary,
listen! I...
120:
There isn't anything special about
me, though.
123:
Someone to distract you from your
loneliness? Could've been anyone.
There's nothing special about me in
particular.
125:
It's not like I'll find anyone else this
convenient anytime soon. Besides, I
don't want to feel lonely again.
126:
The only thing special about us is
how we met. Right?
136:
N-no. That's the first time I've seen
one that looks like that...
143:
These sheep... They're reading
people's minds?
148: ...Oh, crap. This is bad. Really bad!
153: Must be really bad for you, huh...
157:
A ring? Heh, yeah right! There's no
way I'd be able to handle married
life with you, so it's easier to just stay
like this.
159:
Huh?! Is THAT what you were
thinking this whole time? You said
you just wanted to save up money
first!
161:
N-no, honey! This thing is just
spouting off nonsense!
164:
You two can have your little spat
later. Follow the Guild's instructions
and evacuate!
167:
What are these things?! There's no
end to them!
172:
Love me. Hold me tight. Hotter,
stronger, ROUGHER! Here I am... Take
ALL of me!
186:
Yep, that's me, happy with just being
friends forever! Well, if HE comes on
to me first, that's another story. I'd
pounce.
189: Shut UP! Shut up, shut up!
192:
I guess I'll just keep him around.
Nothing like having a convenient
backup boy in your pocket.
